1
00:00:11,262 --> 00:00:12,142
Welcome everyone.

2
00:00:12,582 --> 00:00:13,743
Thanks for joining us.

3
00:00:13,923 --> 00:00:16,504
Welcome to our fourth community forum.

4
00:00:16,524 --> 00:00:20,826
We're going to go through the six options that we're continuing to consider.

5
00:00:20,987 --> 00:00:26,749
We'll have some time for Q&A and then we do want to send everybody out into the foyer to take a look at the designs.

6
00:00:26,789 --> 00:00:27,790
Again, my name is Matt Wright.

7
00:00:28,310 --> 00:00:30,632
I'm an architect and principal in charge with SOMA.

8
00:00:30,872 --> 00:00:33,053
We are the designers for the Medford High School project.

9
00:00:33,093 --> 00:00:37,215
We have been making updates based on all the community feedback that we've received to date.

10
00:00:37,355 --> 00:00:46,481
So the guidance that you'll see here is yes, it's certainly an evolution of the design as we're able to get into more detail now that we just have six options to look at as opposed to 29 options.

11
00:00:47,361 --> 00:00:52,864
So the six options that we've been looking at, these are the versions of them that were coming out of the PDP process.

12
00:00:53,044 --> 00:00:56,306
We have option A.1, which is our code upgrade option.

13
00:00:56,506 --> 00:00:59,628
This is really just fixing the existing building as it stands today.

14
00:00:59,948 --> 00:01:03,370
Option B.1.2, which is one of our addition renovation options.

15
00:01:03,570 --> 00:01:05,871
It maintains the majority of the existing building.

16
00:01:06,091 --> 00:01:10,233
It is trying to salvage as much as the embodied carbon that's present in this building as possible.

17
00:01:10,293 --> 00:01:13,455
That was a primary reason why it was advanced to this next stage of study.

18
00:01:13,815 --> 00:01:16,338
C2.2 is our second addition renovation option.

19
00:01:16,778 --> 00:01:24,246
It preserves the gymnasium, the pool building, as well as a portion of the cafeteria area, the D wing that's out in front of the gymnasium.

20
00:01:24,687 --> 00:01:30,373
C3.4 preserves just the gymnasium and the pool and builds a new addition around those two structures.

21
00:01:32,049 --> 00:01:44,132
D1.1 is our first all-new construction option and that is built down primarily on the southern parking lot when you drive in but also a portion of the existing building because it's too tight to fit the entirety of the building on that parking lot.

22
00:01:44,352 --> 00:01:49,894
And then finally D2.1 is all-new construction as well and it is located primarily on Edgerly Field.

23
00:01:50,054 --> 00:01:58,896
It does spill a little bit down the hill given the fact that Edgerly Field by itself again is not large enough to be able to house the entirety of the new building.

24
00:01:59,471 --> 00:02:01,252
So that's just the overview of where we were.

25
00:02:01,493 --> 00:02:05,115
We did want to land also with this particular topic.

26
00:02:05,336 --> 00:02:12,181
Recently come to the project team's attention that there is a deed restriction on the site that was established back in 1967.

27
00:02:13,001 --> 00:02:16,864
Currently working our way through the implications of what this means.

28
00:02:17,125 --> 00:02:21,408
I will say that it does not mean that three options are immediately off the table.

29
00:02:21,648 --> 00:02:27,234
And it's important to note that the deed restriction is different than an Article 97 open space process.

30
00:02:27,274 --> 00:02:29,816
We have actively reached out to DCR.

31
00:02:29,836 --> 00:02:31,919
We will be continuing the conversations with them.

32
00:02:34,301 --> 00:02:35,943
What other questions do you all have for us?

33
00:02:38,342 --> 00:02:51,735
I think the lessons that we took, we actually deployed on C2.2, 3.4, and D.1, all of which had modular classrooms previously, and we've been able to sort of flip those over to having zero, which is for the positive.

34
00:02:51,835 --> 00:02:58,201
So I really think after looking at it with B1.2 and A.1, there's really no way of avoiding the modular classrooms.

35
00:03:00,681 --> 00:03:02,622
But yes, everyone is talking about this.

36
00:03:02,862 --> 00:03:04,383
Everyone is talking about the cost.

37
00:03:04,423 --> 00:03:14,748
We will be able to share some updated sense of what that is going to be when we get up to this next round of cost estimating that's going to be presented to the building committee next week on Wednesday, May 20th.

38
00:03:15,008 --> 00:03:18,410
I know we're really relying on the expertise of the project's team.

39
00:03:18,750 --> 00:03:33,335
who keep saying, and there were a lot of voices in the community at the last meeting that said, they don't want to see too much cut at this phase, because people are really interested in seeing what will this look like to get the cost estimate.

40
00:03:33,435 --> 00:03:36,296
So we have one chance to get this right, and that's what we're going to try to do.

41
00:03:36,316 --> 00:03:41,918
All right, well, let's go sticker up some boards and talk about what we like and what we don't like.

42
00:03:51,136 --> 00:03:59,759
Thank you for watching!

